        'In a tennis match, the key information structures are things like: opponent\'s grip change as they prepare to serve, weight shift direction before groundstroke, ball toss position relative to body axis, racket face angle in the backswing. These cues reliably predict shot direction, pace, and spin fractions of a second before impact. A skilled player reads these and positions accordingly. The skill of court positioning is not "move to the right place." It\'s "read these specific cues and move in response."',
