        'In a coaching conversation, the key information structures are things like: the moment a client\'s language moves from describing a problem to performing distress about the problem, the specific phrasing they use that reveals their underlying model of the situation, the pause before a statement that signals they\'re about to say something they don\'t quite believe, the energy shift when you\'ve hit the real constraint versus a presenting symptom. A skilled coach reads these and responds. The skill is not "ask good questions." It\'s "read these cues and ask questions that respond to what you\'re reading."',
